# Running App on iPhone 14 Simulator

This plan outlines the steps to create, boot, and run the Flutter application on an iPhone 14 simulator.

## Proposed Changes

### Device Management
- Create an iPhone 14 simulator using `xcrun simctl`.
- Boot the created simulator.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Verify that the iPhone 14 simulator boots successfully.
- Run `flutter run -d <device_id>` and verify the app launches on the simulator.
